1.00	Vishalgad	Vishalgad	Vishalgad (also called Khelna or Khilna) was one of the important forts of Shivaji and Maratha Empire. The name ‘Vishalgad’ meaning grand fort in Marathi, was given by Shivaji after annexing it for the Maratha Empire in 1659.The fort is about 1130 meters that is 3630 feet.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6c/Surviving_Structure_on_Vishalgad.jpg/200px-Surviving_Structure_on_Vishalgad.jpg
